<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT OF DIANA JARVIS</TI>
<P>I, Diana Jarvis, of the Town of Whitby in the Regional Municipality of Durham, Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am assistant to Edward G. Spong, lawyer for the Defendant/Appellant 2487048 Ontario Limited herein.</P>
<P>2. I have reviewed this file and have also personally worked on this file from time to time and as such have knowledge of the matters hereinafter deposed to. Where I do not have personal knowledge of the matters deposed to, I have stated the course of my information, and I verily believe such information to be true.</P>
<P>3. The background of this matter is somewhat unusual.</P>
<P>4. The Plaintiffs/Respondents brought a motion for summary judgment which, after being adjourned from time to time, was ultimately argued on November 2, 2017 in Barrie.</P>
<P>5. In the motion the Plaintiffs/Respondents sought judgment against all the Defendants.</P>
<P>6. The motions court judge, Justice Boswell, reserved judgment.</P>
<P>7. On or about November 27, 2017 Justice Boswell's Reasons were received in our office via e-mail. Justice Boswell granted judgment against 2487048 Ontario Limited but declined to give judgment against Mike Allen or Clark Kent on the basis that the grounds argued by the Plaintiffs/Respondents namely conviction and misrepresentation were not pleaded.</P>
<P>8. In fact, the grounds referred to in the preceding paragraph had been pleaded in an Amended Statement of Claim which Plaintiffs' counsel, through inadvertence, had not included in the Motion Record.</P>
<P>9. Mr. Spong and Mr. Valler [counsel for the Plaintiffs] consulted with one another as to how to properly and best address this issue. They agreed to write to Justice Boswell and advise him of the true state of the pleadings prior to taking out the formal Orders. I am advised by Mr. Spong and do verily believe, that it was his view that, until the formal Order was issued and entered, Justice Boswell was not <EM>functus officio</EM>.</P>
<P>10. As a result of the letter which was sent to Justice Boswell the matter was brought back before him in Newmarket on March 6, 2018. On March 7, 2018, Justice Boswell granted judgment against Mike Allen and Clark Kent. No order has been made against the Defendant Orion Fitness Inc.</P>
<P>11. Mr. Valler attempted to take out one Order incorporating the judgment, set out in the Justice Boswell's Reasons dated November 27, 2017 and the order made by Justice Boswell on March 7, 2018. However, the court staff advised Mr. Valler that it would be necessary to take out two Orders, one dated November 27, 2017 and one dated March 7, 2018. This has now been done.</P>
<P>12. Clark Kent, Mike Allen and 2487048 Ontario Limited all wish to appeal Justice Boswell's orders. To that end, Clark Kent and Mike Allen delivered a Notice of Appeal dated April 4, 2018. Now attached to this my Affidavit and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; are true copies of the Notice of Appeal and my Affidavit of Service, sworn April 11, 2018. 2487048 Ontario Limited also delivered a Notice of Appeal dated April 4, 2018. Now attached to this my Affidavit and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; are true copies of the Notice of Appeal and my Affidavit of Service dated April 11, 2018.</P>
<P>13. The Notice of Appeal of the Defendants/Appellants, Clark Kent and Mike Allan, has been filed.</P>
<P>14. Mr. Spong advises me and I do verily believe, that upon reflection, he realizes that the appropriate process was for the two formal Orders to be taken out. However, he did not direct his mind to that issue when he realized Justice Bowell was not aware of the amended pleading but, rather, concentrated his efforts on correcting that situation.</P>
<P>15. As mentioned in paragraph 12 the Defendant/Appellant 2487048 Ontario Limited does wish to proceed with the appeal. A review of the Notices of Appeal discloses that the issues in the proposed appeal of 2487048 Ontario Limited overlap with the issues raised in the appeal of Clark Kent and Mike Allen.</P>
<P>16. I am advised by Mr. Spong and do verily believe, that if the Defendant/Appellant 2487048 Ontario Limited is not allowed to proceed with its appeal and Clark Kent and Mike Allen are successful there could be, in the end result, inconsistent judgments.</P>
<P>17. Mr. Spong advised Mr. Valler of 2487048 Ontario Limited's intention to appeal by letter dated April 5, 2018. Now attached to this my Affidavit and marked as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; is a true copy of the redacted letter.</P>
<P>18. This Affidavit is made in support of a motion for an order extending the time for the Defendant/Appellant 2487048 Ontario Limited to file its Notice of Appeal and for no improper purpose.</P>
